        <div class="question">What's the difference between mixing and mastering?</div>
        <div class="answer">
            Mixing is the meticulous process of changing the individual tracks/singular instruments in a mix, and audio
            mastering typically only deals with the stereo output of a mix. Music mastering comes in the wake of audio
            mixing and is the last creative and innovative process before releasing a tune or an album. A decent mixing
            and/or mastering engineer can likewise cause an assortment of melodies and vocals to feel like a cohesive
            and coherent project, sticking them all together.
        </div>
    </div>

