            under the circumstances, particularly for Independent (non mainstream) artists. With certain studios this
            isn't possible, yet I'll give a valiant effort to work with my customers and give them the best arrangement
            I can.
            By and large, with regards to mixing, I charge per song. I discover it to be simpler for my work process and
            can ultimately save my clients money . The total mixing price relies upon how complex the mix for the song
            is and how much work should be done to finish the mix. I need to take the time important to get your tune to
            sound as incredible as it should. I like to go through in any event daily or two on most mixes. Removing
            them from the studio, tuning in to them in various conditions and giving existence to permit the blends to
            soak in. I likewise need to ensure that you get two or three rounds of changes. As a result of this it can
            become tedious on my part and I have to charge as needs be. In the event that you have a ton of tunes, I can
            give a break and begin to cut the cost down. Particularly if the melodies are all from a similar meeting and
            have comparable tones between them. Kindly don't hesitate to ask me more data with respect to this.
        </div>
    </div>
