            Yes, IF your mixing is reasonably well done. Music mastering is the final "polish" or "sheen" on a mix, but
            it's not a substitute for good mixing. That being said, I've worked on many CD's that have had less than
            stellar mixes that have turned out sounding amazing after leaving my mastering studio.</div>
